article.headline: Fairfield 89, St. Peter's 78
article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) -- Jonathan Han scored 24 points -- including the game-tying shot late in regulation -- as Fairfield rallied for an 89-78 overtime win over St. Peter's on Friday night. Anthony Johnson added 14 points and 12 rebounds for the Stags (3-8, 1-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), while Herbie Allen, Marty O'Sullivan and Warren Edney had 11 points each. Nick Leon had 15 points -- including three 3-pointers -- and Todd Sowell had 14 points and a game-high 18 rebounds for the Peacocks (3-8, 0-2). Trailing 65-56 with 4:31 left to play, the Stags fought back and closed with a 12-3 run, tying the game at 68-68 on Han's layup with 29 seconds remaining. Each team hit a 3-pointer to open overtime before Fairfield went ahead for good on a 3-pointer by O'Sullivan. Raul Orta hit a layup to cut the lead to 74-73, but the Stags closed out the game with a 15-5 run.
